ary, Cheltenham]]. 1871. p. 40. [[#CITEREFBlacker1890|Gloucestershire Notes and Queries]]. Section 1703. p310.</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* {{Cite book\n | editor-last = Blacker\n | editor-first = Reverend Beaver Henry\n | editor-link = Beaver Henry Blacker\n | title = Gloucestershire Notes and Queries\n | publisher = Simpkin, Marshall, Hamilton, Kent, & Co., Limited\n | volume = 4\n | date = 1890\n | location = London\n | language = English\n | oclc = 982665719\n | url = https://archive.org/details/gloucestershire03unkngoog\n | url-access = registration\n | ref = harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n | author = Great Britain. Parliament. House of Commons\n | date = 1780{{ndash}}1782\n | title = Journals of the House of Commons Volume 38\n | publisher = By order of the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]]\n | location = London\n | language = English\n | oclc = 1751506\n | url = https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=chi.78147432\n | ref = {{sfnref|Journal|1780}}\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n | last = Henderson\n | first = James\n | year = 1994\n | origyear = 1970\n | title = The Frigates: An account of the lighter warships of the Napoleonic wars 1793-1815\n | publisher = [[Leo Cooper]]\n | location = London\n | language = English\n | isbn = 978-0-85052-432-1\n | oclc = 1023686570\n | url-access = registration\n | url = https://archive.org/details/frigatesaccounto0000hend\n | ref = harv\n }}\n* {{Cite book\n | last = James\n | first = William\n | authorlink = William James (naval historian)\n | year = 2002\n | origyear = 1827\n | title = The Naval History of Great Britain: During the French Revolutionary and Napoleonic wars, Volumes 1-6, 1793-1827\n | publisher = [[Conway Publishing|Conway Maritime Press]]\n | location = London\n | isbn = 978-0-85177-905-8\n | oclc = 265568758\n | ref = harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n | last = Tracy\n | first = Nicholas\n | year = 2006\n | title = Who's Who in Nelson's Navy: 200 Naval Heroes\n | publisher = [[Chatham Publishing]]\n | location = London\n | language = English\n | isbn = 978-1-86176-244-3\n | oclc = 62306661\n | ref = harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n | last = White\n | first = Colin\n | authorlink = Colin White (historian)\n | others = The [[1805 Club]]\n | year = 2005\n | title = The Trafalgar Captains: Their Lives and Memorials\n | publisher = [[Chatham Publishing]]\n | location = London\n | language = English\n | isbn = 978-1-86176-247-4\n | oclc = 469507654\n | ref = harv\n}}\n* {{Cite ODNB\n | title = Cooke, John (1763\u20131805), naval officer\n | last1 = Laughton\n | first1 = John Knox\n | authorlink1 = John Knox Laughton\n | others = Revised by [[Andrew Lambert]]\n | year = 2004\n | url = https://www.oxforddnb.com/view/10.1093/ref:odnb/9780198614128.001.0001/odnb-9780198614128-e-6171\n | doi = 10.1093/ref:odnb/6171\n | language = English\n | access-date = 12 April 2020\n | url-status = live\n | url-access = subscription\n | ref = harv\n}}\n* {{Cite archive\n | item = Parish of Saint Mary, Whitechapel, Land Tax Assessment Book\n | item-url = https://search.lma.gov.uk/scripts/mwimain.dll/144/LMA_OPAC/web_detail?SESSIONSEARCH&exp=refd%20CLC/525/MS06015/030\n | item-id = CLC/525/MS06015/030 (former reference MS 06015/30)\n | type = Microfilm\n | date = 1762\n | series = CLC/525/MS06015 - Parish of St Mary Whitechapel: land tax assessment books\n | collection = CLC/525-2 - Land Tax Commissioners for Middlesex, Tower Division\n | repository = [[London Metropolitan Archives]]\n | institution = [[City of London Corporation]]\n | location = 40 Northampton Road, London, England\n | ref = {{sfnref|LandTax|1762}}\n}}\n* {{Cite archive\n | item = Register of Baptisms\n | item-url = https://search.lma.gov.uk/scripts/mwimain.dll/144/LMA_OPAC/web_detail?SESSIONSEARCH&exp=refd%20P93/MRY1/010\n | item-id = P93/Mry1/010 (Microfilm Reference X024/088)\n | type = Microfilm\n | date = 5 March 1762\n | series = Church of England Parish Registers, 1538 to 1812, London, England\n | f