{"title_page": "Vellimon", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=June 2017}}{{Use dmy dates|date = November 2016}}\n\n'''Vellimon''' is a scenic small village situated in [[Perinad]] panchayath of [[Kollam district]] in [[Kerala]]. It is situated around 13&nbsp;km away from district headquarters. Vellimon is a peninsular landmass of laterite soil that is protruding into Ashtamudi lake the peninsula is having a 20 metre high nearly continuous cliff facing backwaters. Farming, fishing and coir manufacturing are major activity in Vellimon. Chief cropping in the area is coconut. The population is overwhelmingly Hindus and there is visible lack of entrepreneurship and organised activities in the area. There were two resorts that came up in Vellimon namely Snehatheeram and Cambay Palm Lagoon. Due to lack of co-operation and anti social activiies from local communities both were forced to shut down. Cambay Palm Lagoon was situated in the scenic laterite cliff that overlooks [[Munroe Island]] this resort is currently vandalised by miscreants.\n[[File:IIFK.jpg|thumb|[[Institute of Fashion Technology Kerala]] in Vellimon, [[Kollam]]]]\nThe major institution in the area is [[Institute of Fashion Technology Kerala|The Institute of Fashion Technology Kerala]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kochi/young-artist-leads-drive-to-turn-ashtamudi-into-ishtamudi/articleshow/68644801.cms|title=Young artist leads drive to turn Ashtamudi into \u2018ishtamudi\u2019 {{!}} Kochi News - Times of India|last=Apr 3|first=Deepa Soman {{!}} Updated:|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14|last3=Ist|first3=12:40}}</ref> There is also a\n\n== History ==\nVellimon is having a place in history because of the legend of ''Vellimon Kottaram temple''. Today nobody will find a ''Kottaram'' or Palace in Vellimon despite people referring to a place in Vellimon as Kottaram. In [[Unnuneeli Sandesam]] there is mentioning about Vellimon. The place is referred to as ''Murithitta'' in the work. This was confirmed by oriental historian Late Mr. [[K. Raghavan Pillai]].\n\n== Politics ==\nVellimon is part of [[Kundara (Assembly constituency)|Kundara]] legislative assembly constituencies in the [[Kollam district|district of Kollam]]. [[J. Mercykutty Amma]] is the current elected member from Kundara constituency and she is one of the sitting ministers in the State Cabinet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elections.in/kerala/assembly-constituencies/2016-election-results.html|title=Kerala Assembly Election - 2016|publisher=Elections.in|accessdate=2018-12-10}}</ref> Vellimon is part of [[Kollam (Lok Sabha constituency)|Kollam Lok Sabha Constituency]]. Vellimon area has strong presence of RSS and CPIM.\n\n== Transport ==\n[[Kundara railway station|Kundara]] is the nearest railway station which is 6.5&nbsp;km away.\n\nMajor transportation is road ways. Public transportation is handled by [[Kerala State Road Transport Corporation]] and Private buses. KSRTC connects Vellimon with Kollam and Trivandrum. Private buses connects Vellimon with Kotiyam, Kundara, Anchalummodu and Kollam.\n\nThere are boat jetties in Vellimon but no formal boat services. There is a countryboat (''kadathuvellam)'' between Vellimon and Perumon on demand.\n\nThe nearest airport is [[Trivandrum International Airport]].\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n<references group=\"\" responsive=\"1\"></references>\n{{commons category|Kundara}}{{Kollam}}{{Kerala|state=collapsed}}{{Kollam district}}\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=June 2017}}{{Use dmy dates|date = November 2016}}\n\n'''Vellimon''' is a scenic small village situated in [[Perinad]] panchayath of [[Kollam district]] in [[Kerala]]. It is situated around 13 km away from district headquarters. Vellimon is a peninsular landmass of laterite soil that is protruding into Ashtamudi lake the peninsula is having a 20 metre high nearly continuous cliff facing backwaters. Farming, fishing and coir manufacturing are major activity in Vellimon. Chief cropping in the area is coconut. The population is overwhelmingly Hindus and there is visible lack of entrepreneurship and organised activities in the area. There were two resorts that came up in Vellimon namely Snehatheeram and Cambay Palm Lagoon. Due to lack of co-operation and anti social activiies from local communities both were forced to shut down. Cambay Palm Lagoon was situated in the scenic laterite cliff that overlooks [[Munroe Island]] this resort is currently vandalised by miscreants.\n[[File:IIFK.jpg|thumb|[[Institute of Fashion Technology Kerala]] in Vellimon, [[Kollam]]]]\nThe major institution in the area is [[Institute of Fashion Technology Kerala|The Institute of Fashion Technology Kerala]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kochi/young-artist-leads-drive-to-turn-ashtamudi-into-ishtamudi/articleshow/68644801.cms|title=Young artist leads drive to turn Ashtamudi into \u2018ishtamudi\u2019 {{!}} Kochi News - Times of India|last=Apr 3|first=Deepa Soman {{!}} Updated:|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14|last3=Ist|first3=12:40}}</ref> There is also a \n\n== History ==\nVellimon is having a place in history because of the legend of ''Vellimon Kottaram temple''. Today nobody will find a ''Kottaram'' or Palace in Vellimon despite people referring to a place in Vellimon as Kottaram. In [[Unnuneeli Sandesam]] there is mentioning about Vellimon. The place is referred to as ''Murithitta'' in the work. This was confirmed by oriental historian Late Mr. [[K. Raghavan Pillai]].\n\n== Politics ==\nVellimon is part of [[Kundara (Assembly constituency)|Kundara]] legislative assembly constituencies in the [[Kollam district|district of Kollam]]. [[J. Mercykutty Amma]] is the current elected member from Kundara constituency and she is one of the sitting ministers in the State Cabinet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elections.in/kerala/assembly-constituencies/2016-election-results.html|title=Kerala Assembly Election - 2016|publisher=Elections.in|accessdate=2018-12-10}}</ref> Vellimon is part of [[Kollam (Lok Sabha constituency)|Kollam Lok Sabha Constituency]]. Vellimon area has strong presence of RSS and CPIM.\n\n== Transport ==\n[[Kundara railway station|Kundara]] is the nearest railway station which is 6.5 km away.\n\nMajor transportation is road ways. Public transportation is handled by [[Kerala State Road Transport Corporation]] and Private buses. KSRTC connects Vellimon with Kollam and Trivandrum. Private buses connects Vellimon with Kotiyam, Kundara, Anchalummodu and Kollam.\n\nThere are boat jetties in Vellimon but no formal boat services. There is a countryboat (''kadathuvellam)'' between Vellimon and Perumon on demand.\n\nThe nearest airport is [[Trivandrum International Airport]].\n\n== References ==\n<references group=\"\" responsive=\"1\"></references>\n{{commons category|Kundara}}{{Kollam}}{{Kerala|state=collapsed}}{{Kollam district}}\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up, addeduncategorisedtag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vellimon"}
